						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#160;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185; (Lemures) is a horror game from Japan. The game can be played solitaire or as a two player co-operative game. The player is exploring a strange fantastic castle, helping souls trapped, and seeking their own way out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The publisher says:&amp;#10;Is there a place for the soul to return here? The abyss is changing. You will always be exposed to the threat of unknown beings in the castle. Explore the interior of the old castle while rejecting &amp;quot;they&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Since the inside of the castle changes with each play, different developments will come every time. Co-operative play with two people is also possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During your exploration, you may find the souls of those who once lived in the castle. Such a soul is already a light in front of the wind, but if you give it power, it will bloom beautiful flowers. On the contrary, if you take power, it will soon die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You cannot survive in the castle without strong power. Let's create a new technique from Reason and Instinct. There is some danger in learning the art of Instinct. The ending changes depending on whether you follow Reason or Instinct.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have been exploring the castle for a long time, you will be oppressed by karma. Karma is a dangerous being that undermines vitality and soul. Be careful, but be quick to explore. The deeper you go into the castle, the more memories of the past will come back ...&amp;#10;publisher's summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
